28.a
These astonishing'ly' beautiful gift's' were present'ed' by Ann'’s' old'er' brother.
Which of the underlined morphemes is a derivational morpheme?
    -ly                 Derivational Morpheme            
    -s                  Infletional Morpheme: Plurality
    -ed                 Infletional Morpheme: Past Participle
    -’s                 Infletional Morpheme: Possessive Case
    -er                 Infletional Morpheme: Comparative


    Free Morpheme:          happy
    Bound Morpheme:         cats         ---> -s: bound morpheme
        - Derivational morpheme: Word turn into another grammatical type
                Derivational morphemes: -er, un-/im-, -ness, re-, -ize
        - Infletional morpheme:
                  Possessive Case
                  Progressive
                  Plurality
                  Comparative
                  Superlative
                  Past Participle
    Lexical Morpheme:       unhappiness  ---> happy: a lexical morpheme
    Grammatical Morpheme:   happily      ---> -ly: a grammatical morpheme  


