48.d
Below are statements by English language teachers about their role in the classroom. 
Each teacher adopts a different method/approach in teaching English.
    In which option is there a mismatch between the method/approach and the corresponding teacher’s role?

        The Grammar-Translation Method – My main role is to help my learners read and write in English, and I’m the authority in the classroom.
        The Audio-Lingual Method – My main role is to direct the language behaviour of my learners. 
                                  I should provide a good role model, and the learners should become good imitators.
        Desuggestopedia – I’m responsible for creating a cheerful learning environment for my learners. If they trust me, they can feel more secure.
        Community Language Learning – Error correction is important as errors lead to the formation of bad habits. So, I immediately correct them when they occur.
        Communicative Language Teaching – Facilitating communication is my ultimate goal as a teacher.  To this end, my main responsibility is to create situations that are likely to promote interaction.

