Regarding this fact, Mr Roach shows the following phrases to his intermediate-level students:
     my turn /maɪ tɜ:n/ (the aɪ diphthong is longer in ‘my’, t is fully aspirated when initial in ‘turn')
     might earn /maɪt ɜ:n/ (the aɪ diphthong is shorter in ‘might’, t is unaspirated when final in ‘might’)
Which feature of pronunciation is being taught by Mr Roach through the examples above?
    Elision 
    Intrusion
    Assimilation 
    Dissimilation
    Juncture

