Below are examples of different methods of vocabulary organisation:
     shopping bag – cashier – change – trolley
     body – arms/legs – fingers/toes
     food – vegetable – cabbage
     hot/cold – happy/sad
Which of the following methods of vocabulary organisation is not exemplified in the list above?
    Presenting hierarchies with hyponyms
    Forming groups of thematically-related words
    Listing words with similar morphological properties
    Introducing words through antonymy 
    Establishing relations of wholes to parts

