Below are some common problems in writing multiple-choice items to test vocabulary:
  I. Distractors with opposite meanings can easily be ruled out.
  II. The correct answer does not belong to the same grammatical category as the distractors.
  III. The correct answer differs from the distractors in terms of lexical difficulty and frequency.
  IV. The wording in the stem is ambiguous, so it does not help to find the correct answer.
Which of the problems can be found in the item above?
    I and II 
    I and III
    II and III 
    II and IV
    III and IV

